<HEADLINE>
E.G. LOWRY JR., 95, INSURANCE EXECUTIVE 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Fla. )  (js) 
 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Edward George Lowry Jr., a former chairman and president of
General Reinsurance Corp., died Aug. 11 at Sarasota Memorial
Hospital in Sarasota, Fla. He was 95.
</P>
<P>
   Lowry was named president of General Reinsurance and its fire
insurance affiliate, North Star Reinsurance, in 1946, and chairman
four years later. After he stepped aside as chairman in 1960, Lowry
was a director and chairman of the company's executive and finance
committees. He retired in 1964.
</P>
<P>
   Lowry, a Rhodes scholar, received a bachelor's degree from
Harvard University in 1925 and graduated with honors from Balliol
College of Oxford University in 1928. He got a law degree from
Columbia University in 1929. His legal career included positions as
an associate at Hale &AMP; Dorr, in the law division of Reconstruction
Finance Corp., and general counsel of Maryland Casualty. He was the
treasurer of ER Squibb from 1943 to 1946, before joining General
Reinsurance.
</P>
<P>
   He is survived by his wife, Ruth, of Sarasota; a daughter, Ruth
Arnold, of Novato, Calif.; a son, Edward George III, of New Castle,
Wash.; six grandchildren and six great-grandchildren.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
