<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-CARDINALS-FASSEL-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TOBIN DEFENDS FASSEL'S USE OF SEAHORN TO RETURN KICKS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By STEVE SCHOENFELD  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Cardinals Coach Vince Tobin has come to the defense of the New
York Giants' Jim Fassel, under fire for using Pro Bowl cornerback
Jason Seahorn as a kick-return specialist.
</P>
<P>
   Seahorn suffered torn anterior cruciate and medial collateral
ligaments in his right knee in Thursday night's preseason game
against the New York Jets and will be lost for the season.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm sure it's a blow to them,'' Tobin said of the injury
Seahorn suffered in his first-ever pro kickoff return. ``But it's
just an unfortunate thing. You face a two-edged sword. You have to
get guys ready to play. You hope you do not get injuries. But you
can't just not play.
</P>
<P>
   ``You have to be aware of keeping players healthy. But you can't
be spooked every time you go out there. You can get hurt just
stepping off a bus. You can get hurt in pregame warm-ups. I've had
all those things happen . . . Pretty soon you're chasing ghosts and
afraid of your own shadow, and you don't want that.''
</P>
<P>
   Tobin pointed out that some of the NFL's top defensive backs
have had great success as returners, including Deion Sanders and
Rod Woodson.
</P>
<P>
   ``When you're on the firing line, you have to make decisions,''
Tobin said. ``If they don't (pan) out, you're going to get
second-guessed.''
</P>
<P>
   Several Giants players have questioned Fassel's decision to use
Seahorn as a returner, saying it wasn't worth the risk.
</P>
<P>
   Former Giants quarterback Dave Brown, who played for Fassel last
season before signing with the Cardinals in the off-season,
understands why Fassel decided to use Seahorn on special teams.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's something (Jason) always wanted to do,'' Brown said. ``He
has been lobbying for it for three years. It's just one of those
fluke things. The coach's job is to upgrade the team. The Giants
finished last in kickoff returns last year. Why not do it?'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-22-98 0039EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19980822.0017 </DOCNO>
