<P>
   BBN-WOHLERS-PROFILE _ Mark Wohlers, 28, has been a major league
star since 1991 _ a relief pitcher for the Atlanta Braves, and
among the hardest throwers in the history of the game. Capable of
overpowering hitters with a 100-mph fastball, he saved 97 games for
Atlanta spanning 1995 and 1997. But earlier this year, Wohlers
suddenly lost his ability to throw strikes. By Bruce Weber. (With
color photo.)
</P>
<P>
   (We plan to move the story by 1:15 p.m. ET in ``s'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   NY-BADDREAM-HOUSE (Sagaponack, N.Y.) _ Ira Rennert's dream house
in the Hamptons will have 29 bedrooms, 39 bathrooms, a 164-seat
theater and a restaurant-sized kitchen with five refrigerators, six
sinks and a 1,500-gallon grease trap. The 63-acre, five-building
spread, at the rim of the Atlantic Ocean here, will dwarf the White
House, San Simeon and Bill Gates' mega-mansion. Can a complex of
such staggering dimensions be considered a single-family home? This
is the question being asked by the Sagaponack Homeowners'
Association, an ad hoc group of wealthy residents who are
challenging Rennert's building permits, granted in the dead of
winter when his prospective neighbors were 100 miles away in
Manhattan. By Jane Gross.
</P>
