<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, Aug. 23 and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact William Toren at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   BIZARRE-BURB (Lake Los Angeles) _ Somewhere between the postcard
ideal of small-town America and a weirder, more disturbing reality
lies the quiet Antelope Valley community of Lake Los Angeles.
Eighty miles north of its metropolitan namesake and 25 miles from
the nearest post office, this high-desert bedroom 'burb of 14,000
is a place of extreme, even surreal contrasts. By Reed Johnson.
(Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   XXX &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
