<P>
   BBC-ALUMINUM-BATS (Undated) _ Aluminum alloy bats _ made of a
space-age technology _ have come to dominate and alter the nature
of amateur baseball in the United States by being simply too good:
The bats are far lighter to swing than wood and the ball flies off
faster and harder. Last week the NCAA said that the newest
generation of these bats has become dangerous to players because of
reduced reaction times to hit balls and harmful to the game because
so many hitting records are being broken. The NCAA ordered bat
manufacturers to modify their designs to fit a new
lower-performance standard. The group that regulates high school
sports said it is considering a similar move. By Ed Guzman and Kirk
Johnson.
</P>
