fide major league star, capable of overpowering major league
hitters with a 100-mile per hour fastball, he saved 97 games for
Atlanta between 1995 and 1997. But earlier this year he suddenly
lost his ability to throw strikes and as the summer has gone on and
he has twice been demoted to the minor leagues, his control has
only become more and more erratic, his appearances alarmingly
sprinkled with pitches that bounce before the plate or soar to the
backstop. By Bruce Weber. Page 1 story.
