   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-RUBLE_ MOSCOW _ In devaluing the ruble on Monday, the
other shoe has dropped for the Russian economy. It has been in
turmoil for several months now -- with some analysts predicting
that a complete collapse could be imminent -- and the Yeltsin
government hopes that finally devaluing the ruble will calm things
down. But even if it does, for how long? The basic underlying
problems of the Russian economy have not changed. (Holmes, Cox News
Service).
</P>
