<P>
   CHINA-SATELLITES _ WASHINGTON _ Critics of the Clinton White
House have had a field day with the president's 1996 decision to
transfer the jurisdiction of approving commercial satellite exports
from the U.S. State Department to the business-friendly Commerce
Department. Republicans have attacked the transfer, saying Clinton
did so as the result of hefty campaign donations from satellite
makers like Loral Corp. But what is not so well-known is how this
jurisdictional transfer away from the more stringent State, to the
Commerce Department was really a bipartisan affair. In fact,
records obtained by the Cox News Service show that key Republicans
in Congress, including House Speaker Newt Gingrich, were behind the
transfer and advocated on behalf of the satellite makers. ``There
is no doubt that the Republicans were helping us do this just as
much as the Clinton White House,'' said Clayton Maury, head of the
Satellite Industry Association. (Carr, Cox News Service).
