Zito, president of the New York Nomads chapter of the Hell's Angels
motorcycle club. In his 45 years, Zito has been many things: outlaw
biker, convict, bodyguard to the stars and stunt man. Now, Zito is
trying to leap from macho man to movie star. Last winter, Zito won
his best role yet, a part in ``Oz,'' a prison drama series on HBO
in which he plays an enforcer for a group of Italian inmates. ``I
watch a lot of these actors and say to myself, 'I could do it
better,'''he says. ``They're trying to look like what I really
am.'' (Edward Keating/New York Times Photo)
