<P>
   (NYT7) NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. -- Aug. 22, 1998 --
NY-BIKER-MOVIESTAR, 8-22 -- Chuck Zito, president of the New York
Nomads chapter of the Hell's Angels motorcycle club. In his 45
years, Zito has been many things: outlaw biker, convict, bodyguard
to the stars and stunt man. Now, Zito is trying to leap from macho
man to movie star. Last winter, Zito won his best role yet, a part
in ``Oz,'' a prison drama series on HBO in which he plays an
enforcer for a group of Italian inmates. ``I watch a lot of these
actors and say to myself, 'I could do it better,'''he says.
``They're trying to look like what I really am.'' (Edward
Keating/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT6) SAGAPONACK, N.Y. -- Aug. 22, 1998 -- NY-BADDREAM-HOUSE,
8-22 -- Land being cleared for Ira Rennert's dream house in
Sagaponack, N.Y. The house will be the largest home in America,
dwarfing the White House and Bill Gates' megamansion. It will have
29 bedrooms, 39 bathrooms, a 164-seat theater and a
restaurant-sized kitchen with five refrigerators. The question
being asked by the Sagaponack Homeowners' Association, which is
challenging Rennert's building permits, is can such a complex be
considered a single-family home? (Lois Raimondo/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
